docs.abstract: Do you fancy yourself a stockpicker? Are you certain you can assess avalanche risk in the backcountry? You may need a lesson in self-serving biases.
docs.snippet: Do you fancy yourself a stockpicker? Are you certain you can assess avalanche risk in the backcountry? You may need a lesson in self-serving biases.
docs.lead_paragraph: When I lived in the mountains of Utah, I used to ski in the backcountry often. This is not resort skiing, and there is no patrol checking for avalanche risk, so assessing that risk becomes your own responsibility. It is an imprecise science, and there is always a chance you’ll get it wrong.

headline.main: You Are Probably Overconfident. (If You Skip This, Doubly So.)
